                  <handDesc>
                    <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="rubrication">
                           <ref target="#ms_i1.1 #ms_i1.2 #ms_i1.3"/>
                          <foreign xml:lang="gez">እግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                          <note>Occasionally <foreign xml:lang="gez">እግዚአብሔር፡</foreign> is in alternating letters of red and black ink (<locus target="#20r #20v #23r #23v #24r #25v #27r #27v #28r #28v" facs="022 023 025 026 028 029 030 031">fols. 20r, 20v, 23r, 23v, 24r, 25v, 27r, 27v, 28r, 28v</locus>, etc.)</note>
                           <ref target="#ms_i1.4 #msi_1.5"/>
                          <foreign xml:lang="gez">ማርያም፡</foreign>
                        </seg>
                        <desc>Columetric layout of text: <locus target="#111v" facs="114">fol. 111v</locus> <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT2000Mazmur#Ps150"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT2000Mazmur#Ps150</span></ref>; <locus target="#120v #121r #121v" facs="123 124">120v, 121r, 121v</locus> <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1566hababa#ThreeYouths3"><span xmlns="" class="w3-tag w3-red">No item: LIT1566hababa#ThreeYouths3</span></ref></desc>
                    </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <summary>Miniatures, all in twentieth-century hand</summary>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1">
                        <locus target="#ir(ecto) #iir(ecto)" facs="001 002">Fols. ir(ecto), iir(ecto)</locus>
                        <desc>Crude drawings of faces and figures</desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2">
                        <locus target="#iiv(erso)" facs="003">Fol. iiv(erso)</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1035HolyMan">Holy Man Portrait</ref> standing with arms upraised
                        </desc>
                        <note>The style of artwork and the pose is reminiscent of the ground hornbill painter’s work as seen in
                        Bodleian MS. Aeth. e. 28, f. 1v (see Demeke and Delamarter, Plate 9, p. 148). A piece of cloth is sewn to the top of the folio to
                        provide cover for the miniature</note>
                      </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d3">
                        <locus target="#137v" facs="140">Fol. 137v</locus>
                        <desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/AT1013EvaPortrait">Evangelist Portrait</ref>, copying a gospel
                        </desc>
                     </decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="frame" xml:id="d4">
                      Decorative designs: <locus target="#1v #7r #14v #22v #32r #39r #44v #53r #59r #63v #71r #76r #88v #98v #101v #106v #112r #124v" facs="004 009 017 025 034 041 047 055 061 066 073 078 091 104 109 114 127">fols. 1v, 7r, 14v, 22v, 32r, 39r, 44v, 53r, 59r, 63v, 71r, 76r, 88v, 98v, 101v, 106v, 112r, 124v</locus> (<foreign xml:lang="gez">ሐረግ፡</foreign> in red and black and brown ink);
                      <locus target="#136r #140r #141v #143v #144v" facs="138 142 144 146 147">136r, 140r, 141v, 143v, 144v</locus>, (alternating red and black dots).
                    </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#ir(ecto)" facs="001">Fol. ir(ecto)</locus> pen trial</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#iv(erso)" facs="002">Fol. iv(erso)</locus>, in faint purple ink: List of names</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e3">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#145v" facs="148">Fol. 145v</locus> scrawls</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e4">
                           <desc>
                              <locus target="#59r" facs="061">Fol. 59r</locus>
                        Several devices mark the midpoint of the psalms:
                        1) the letters of the words of the line are written in alternating red and black ink;
                        2) A symbol inside a box with the word, <foreign xml:lang="gez">መንፈቅ፡</foreign>;
                        and 3) the word <foreign xml:lang="gez">ዝየ፡</foreign> apparently added after the other indications</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e5">
                           <desc>
                          Scribal intervention: words of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#11v #21v #33r #34v #62r" facs="014 024 035 037 064">folss. 11v, 21v, 33r, 34v, 62r, </locus>, etc.);
                          and lines of text are written interlinearly (<locus target="#13v #18v #57r #106v" facs="016 021 059 109">13v, 18v, 57r, 106v, </locus>, etc.);
                          and in the fore edge margin with a symbol (+) marking the location where the text is to be inserted (<locus target="#59r" facs="061">f. 59r, line 9</locus>; <locus target="#63r" facs="065"> f. 63r, line 13</locus>),
                          and in another case where the symbol (+) is used interlinearly to point to a text written interlinearly (<locus target="#121r" facs="123"> f. 121r, line 14</locus>);
                          erasure markings are visible (<locus target="#138v #140v #141v" facs="141 143 144">138v, 140v, 141v, </locus>, etc.);
                          text has been removed (<locus target="#29v #39v #53r" facs="032 042 055">29v, 39v, 53r</locus>, etc.)
                        </desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e6">
                           <desc>
                          This scribe has avoided the problem of lines of text too long to fit on one line by adopting an aspect ratio that leaves ample room
                          for the width of most lines. On a few occasions, the line would have been too long and the scribe finishes the end of the line with
                          words written smaller so as to avoid leftover text (e.g., <locus target="#7v #9r #9v #22r #22v" facs="010 011 012 024 025">folss. 7v, 9r, 9v, 22r, 22v, </locus>).  Occasionally a line is still too long and has to be
                          completed above or below the end of the line (e.g., <locus target="#1r #2v #22r #27r" facs="003 005 024 029">1r, 2v, 22r, 27r</locus>)
                        </desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                  </additions>
